The paper introduces a new language that combines neural networks and probabilistic logic programming, which falls under the intersection of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses program induction and learning from examples, which are common topics in natural language processing (cs.CL) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the theoretical and experimental aspects of the proposed framework, which could also fall under cryptography and security (cs.CR) as it involves analyzing the strengths and weaknesses of the framework.
